## §A.6 Stage-1+ hardware path  (post-RSC, **out of code-layer scope**)

The region the RSC (`verify/*.hexa`) loop **cannot** close. After v1.0.0 code-layer
closure, the hardware / external-bound path toward v2.0.0 — funding · external
validation · phantom-skull bench rigs · in-vivo trials.

| step | content | target | RSC-able? | artifact |
|:----:|:--------|:-------|:---------:|:---------|
| 1 | external collab decision (neuro-eng lab w/ MEG + TMS rigs) | 2026-Q4 | ✗ | MOU |
| 2 | funding round (RT-SC coil fab + phantom skull rig + MEG/OPM diagnostics) | 2027-Q1 | ✗ | grant / investment |
| 3 | Stage-1 simulation parity (full Maxwell coil-field FEM + bioheat FEM + neuron-population response) | ~2026-12 | **partial** (`.hexa` T2 expansion) | `numerics_*_fem.hexa`-class scripts, sim-parity report |
| 4 | Stage-2/3 bench build + cadaver-skull / non-human-primate validation (years out) | ~2027-Q3+ | ✗ | firmware · HDL · PCB · BOM · calibration logs · raw recordings |
| 5 | regulatory: FDA/KFDA class III pre-submission → IDE → first-in-human | ~2028+ | ✗ | 510(k)/PMA dossier, IRB approvals, clinical-trial data |

Step 3 is the last layer this repo can directly touch. Steps 1/2/4/5 are
hardware-ops · external-stakeholder · multi-year work — not closable by
cron/loop firing. §A.6 is `tracking only`; progress cross-referenced into §A.3.

**Current (2026-05-10) status**: all steps unstarted. v2.0.0 = paper design.
`clip/doc/mastoid-clip.md` §X "first-in-world proposal" + `safety/doc/cortical-safety.md`
§X "regulatory pathway" are the starting points for the build-candidate BOM.

### §A.6.1 recommended pre-work order (A → B → C → D)

| stage | content | artifact | external HW? | RSC-able? | value |
|:-----:|:--------|:---------|:------------:|:---------:|:------|
| A | paper-design hardening — `clip/doc/benchtop_v0_design.md` (BOM + block diagram + interface table + safety spec) | `.md` ×1–3 + ASCII/TikZ figs | ✗ | ✓ docs-layer | until funding pitch deck |
| B | Stage-1 simulation parity (= §A.6 step 3) — coil-field FEM + bioheat + neuron-population, FEMM / SimNIBS / Sim4Life published-case parity | `verify/numerics_*_fem.hexa` ×1–3 | ✗ | ✓ partial-RSC | external-collab meeting card |
| C | sim-firmware — coil-driver DAC / EEG-watchdog ADC chain modelled sim-only, no hardware-in-the-loop | `firmware/sim/*.hexa` | ✗ | partial ✓ | prototype of the real MCU firmware |
| D | HDL / MCU skeleton — FPGA coil-timing controller (Verilog) + MCU watchdog (Rust/C). Compiles OK, no flash target | `firmware/hdl/*.v` + `firmware/mcu/*.rs` | ✗ now / ✓ later | ✗ | start when board arrives |

A/B do not break repo regression invariants — `saturation_check` stays PASS,
`falsifier_check` stays 100 % closure, `cli verify all` monotone non-decreasing.
Never PASS→FAIL. C is the first non-`.hexa` file layer — isolate in
`firmware/sim/`. D → separate repo or `firmware/` sub-tree.

