## §B Falsifier detail tables

> **Status (raw#10 honest C3)**: all 4 falsifiers academically UNPROVEN at
> v1.0.0. Each ships in-tree spec + 3-tier (T1/T2/T3) closure tracking. CLI
> sentinel PASS validates lattice arithmetic + token consistency + published-ref
> *parity arithmetic*, NOT in-vivo apparatus or regulatory clearance. Falsifier
> monotone: OPEN → CONFIRMED or OPEN → DEMOTED. Silent retract forbidden.

### §B.1 F-AURA-1 — clip (mastoid form-factor)

Spec: `clip/doc/mastoid-clip.md` · Verb: `hexa-aura clip` · T1 `calc_clip` · T2 `numerics_clip` · T3 `numerics_clip_parity`

| ID         | Falsifier                                                                                          | Status |
|------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| F-AURA-1a  | a 3.6 g/side passive anchor cannot hold position on the mastoid against jaw/chewing motion          | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-1b  | RT-SC coil + driver + battery + radio cannot fit in σ·n/10 = 3.6 g at hearing-aid-BTE density       | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-1c  | bone-conduction back-channel cannot survive being hidden under hair (no skin-contact mic/speaker)   | OPEN   |

n=6 encoding: φ=2 clips, σ·n/10 = 3.6 g/side → n·n/10 = 7.2 g pair (AirPods-Pro 5.4 g class),
sopfr=5 mm bone window, τ=4-point anchor (helix root · mastoid tip · ear-canal entry · concha).

### §B.2 F-AURA-2 — coil (RT-SC nano-coil tile)

Spec: `coil/doc/rt-sc-nanocoil.md` · Verb: `hexa-aura coil` · T1 `calc_coil` · T2 `numerics_coil` · T3 `numerics_coil_parity` · Cross-link: `hexa-rtsc`

| ID         | Falsifier                                                                                          | Status |
|------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| F-AURA-2a  | a μ=1 μm pitch RT-SC tile cannot reach the ∂B/∂x focal gradient TMS-class cortical write needs       | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-2b  | σ²=144 ch/tile read SNR is below OPM-MEG (≈15 fT/√Hz) noise floor through 5 mm bone                  | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-2c  | the coil's switching power dissipates > the 3.6 g clip thermal budget allows (ΔT > 0.5 K at scalp)  | OPEN   |

n=6 encoding: μ=1 μm litho pitch, σ²=144 ch/tile, J₂=24 bidirectional ch/macro-tile,
n^τ=6⁴=1296-ch hex lattice, σ³=1728-electrode-equivalent, RT-SC @ ambient (hexa-rtsc cross-link).

### §B.3 F-AURA-3 — cortex (direct cortical read/write)

Spec: `cortex/doc/cortical-interface.md` · Verb: `hexa-aura cortex` · T1 `calc_cortex` · T2 `numerics_cortex` · T3 `numerics_cortex_parity` · Cross-link: `hexa-brain` (working pipeline)

| ID         | Falsifier                                                                                          | Status |
|------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| F-AURA-3a  | A1 auditory injection cannot match cochlear-implant intelligibility (Cochlear Nucleus 22-ch parity) | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-3b  | V1~V6 injection cannot exceed Argus-II / Orion (60-electrode) effective-pixel count → AR-glass parity fails | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-3c  | S1 haptic write cannot reach Flesher-2016 ICMS taxel density → e-skin replacement fails              | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-3d  | aggregate read decode WPM stays below Willett/Metzger-2023 speech-BCI (≈62–78 WPM)                   | OPEN   |

n=6 encoding: σ=12 cortical target zones, τ=4 operating modes, 6 pyramidal layers, φ=2 bidirectional,
sopfr=5 ms closed-loop latency, σ·τ=48 K virtual-retina pixels (scales by σ powers per tile count).

### §B.4 F-AURA-4 — safety (current-density / SAR / heating / seizure / no-craniotomy)

Spec: `safety/doc/cortical-safety.md` · Verb: `hexa-aura safety` · T1 `calc_safety` · T2 `numerics_safety` · T3 `numerics_safety_parity`

| ID         | Falsifier                                                                                          | Status |
|------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| F-AURA-4a  | continuous-wear induced charge density exceeds Shannon k≤1.5 (and k≤1.85) cortical damage limit      | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4b  | local 10 g-avg SAR exceeds ICNIRP-2020 / IEEE-C95.1-2019 2 W/kg at F-AURA-2 write field strengths    | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4c  | scalp/cortex steady-state heating exceeds ΔT ≤ 0.5 K (CEM43 thermal-dose) limit                      | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4d  | EEG-watchdog seizure-detection ROC cannot reach the μ=1 → 1 % false-alarm floor at clinical sensitivity | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4e  | device is not MRI-conditional (RF heating / displacement-force / image-artifact fails IEC 60601 / ASTM F2503) | OPEN   |

n=6 encoding: Shannon k ≤ sopfr/τ ≈ 1.25 → rounded design target ≤ 1.5; SAR ≤ φ = 2 W/kg;
ΔT ≤ φ/τ = 0.5 K; coating lifetime φ·σ = 24 yr; μ=1 → 1 % watchdog false-alarm floor; τ=4-layer biocompatible coating.

### §B.5 Aggregate

- Total falsifiers preregistered: **4 top-level** (F-AURA-1/2/3/4) decomposed into **15 sub-IDs**
  (F-AURA-1a..c, -2a..c, -3a..d, -4a..e).
- All status: **OPEN** at v1.0.0.
- Closure ladder per top-level falsifier: T1 (`verify/calc_<pillar>.hexa` on disk) +
  T2 (`verify/numerics_<pillar>.hexa` on disk) + T3 (`verify/numerics_<pillar>_parity.hexa` on disk)
  → `closure_pct ∈ {0, 33, 67, 100}` per `runnable_surface_recipe.md` §3.
- v1.0.0 target: all 4 at T1 ✓ + T2 ✓ + T3 ✓ = 100 % code-layer closure. T4 (Stage-1+ in-vivo) = §A.6, out of RSC scope.
